### Use simple words

Create content that all customers can understand, regardless of their ability, level of literacy, expertise, gender, age group or cultural background.

```jsx
<div>
  <h4 className="typography-body-10 text-muted mb-3">FOR EXAMPLE:</h4>
  <p className="typography-body-10 mb-2 ml-4">
    <span className="text-success font-bold">Do:</span> get, start
  </p>
  <p className="typography-body-10 ml-4">
    <span className="text-danger font-bold">Don't:</span> acquire, commence
  </p>
</div>
```

Consider your audience when using words like ‘very’, ‘really’, ‘highly’ or ‘simply’, as each person’s perception or ability to complete a task may be different.

```jsx
<div>
  <h4 className="typography-body-10 text-muted mb-3">FOR EXAMPLE:</h4>
  <p className="typography-body-10 mb-2 ml-4">
    <span className="text-success font-bold">Do:</span> It’s easy to manage your savings goals.
  </p>
  <p className="typography-body-10 mb-2 ml-4">
    <span className="text-danger font-bold">Don't:</span> It’s really easy to manage your savings goals.
  </p>
  <p className="typography-body-10 ml-4">
    <span className="text-danger font-bold">Don't:</span> Simply scan your bill and we’ll do the rest.
  </p>
</div>
```

Avoid industry jargon, complex language or [abbreviations](/content/guidelines/abbreviation) that aren’t commonly used. If it’s necessary to use any of these, consider including an explanation.

Don't use slang to shorten words.

```jsx
<div>
  <h4 className="typography-body-10 text-muted mb-3">FOR EXAMPLE:</h4>
  <p className="typography-body-10 mb-2 ml-4">
    <span className="text-success font-bold">Do:</span> afternoon
  </p>
  <p className="typography-body-10 ml-4">
    <span className="text-danger font-bold">Don't:</span> arvo
  </p>
</div>
```

---

### Keep it brief

Every word should serve a purpose. If it doesn’t, remove it. See how many words you can omit without losing your key message or meaning. Read it out loud to check if it sounds right.

```jsx
<div>
  <h4 className="typography-body-10 text-muted mb-3">FOR EXAMPLE:</h4>
  <p className="typography-body-10 mb-2 ml-4">
    <span className="text-success font-bold">Do:</span> You're connected
  </p>
  <p className="typography-body-10 ml-4">
    <span className="text-danger font-bold">Don't:</span> The connection has been established successfully
  </p>
</div>
```

Include only one idea per sentence.

Use short headings and visual cues to help with context, scanning and memory.

Sometimes, a longer message may be helpful, for example, when there’s an extended wait and we want to give the customer an idea of what’s happening.

```jsx
<div>
  <h4 className="typography-body-10 text-muted mb-3">FOR EXAMPLE:</h4>
  <p className="typography-body-10 mb-2 ml-4">
    <span className="text-success font-bold">Do:</span> We’re getting things ready for you
  </p>
  <p className="typography-body-10 ml-4">
    <span className="text-danger font-bold">Don't:</span> Please wait
  </p>
</div>
```

